                                        <li><strong>Pick fundamentally good stocks</strong>
                                    </div>
                                    <br> Once you’ve identified your goals, the next step is to start picking the right stocks for your portfolio. When executing this step, make sure to focus on fundamentally strong companies. They’re the ones that are
                                    stable, less volatile, and more likely to generate stellar returns over the long-term. No matter how attractive a company may look from the outside, if it doesn’t back it up with strong financials and fundamentals,
                                    it is less likely to do well in the future.
                                    </li>
                                </div>
                            </div>
